problems.description:
Implement optimistic locking with @Version to handle concurrent updates.

```java
@Entity class Product {
    @Id Long id;
    String name;
    int stock;
    @Version Long version; // auto-managed by JPA
}

// Concurrent update scenario:
// Thread A reads: product {stock=10, version=1}
// Thread B reads: product {stock=10, version=1}
// Thread A saves: stock=9, version becomes 2 (OK)
// Thread B tries to save stock=9 with version=1:
//   → OptimisticLockException: version mismatch!

// Handle:
try {
    productRepo.save(product);
} catch (OptimisticLockException e) {
    // Reload and retry
    product = productRepo.findById(id).get();
    product.setStock(product.getStock() - 1);
    productRepo.save(product);
}
```

**Key insight:** `@Version` adds `WHERE version=N` to UPDATE/DELETE. No DB-level locks — optimistic (assumes low contention). Throws on conflict instead of blocking.

